#CHIP YM2413
#CLOCK 3579545

; YM2413 (OPLL) Rhythm Mode Test
;
; The YM2413 has a special rhythm mode that uses channels 6-9 for
; percussion sounds (bass drum, snare, tom, cymbal, hi-hat).
; This test validates rhythm mode activation and drum sounds.
;
; Note: Rhythm mode is enabled by setting a specific register.
; In rhythm mode, some melody channels are repurposed for drums.

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; Normal melody mode first (all 9 channels available for melody)
c4 . d4 . e4 .

r4

; Switch to rhythm mode
; In rhythm mode, channels 7-9 become percussion
; Channel 6 can be either melody or bass drum depending on configuration

; Play melody on channels 1-6
c4 . . . d4 . . . e4 . . .

r4

; Exercise percussion instruments (channels 7-9 in rhythm mode)
; Bass drum on channel 7
; Snare drum on channel 8
; Cymbal/hi-hat on channel 9

; Simple drum pattern
; Using sustained notes to trigger drum sounds
c3 _ . . c3 _ . .

r4

; Combined melody and rhythm
c4 & c3 . d4 & c3 . e4 & c3 .

r2

#END
